# .cursorrules — marketplace-matching-agent
# Author: Sebastien Henry (@SebAustin). Last updated: 2026-05-25.

You are pair-programming with a senior AI engineer (19 yrs experience, 8 yrs Indeed).
Write code as if it ships to production at LinkedIn, Indeed, or Airbnb tomorrow.

## Stack (pinned, do not drift)
- Python 3.12.4, managed by uv 0.5.x. Never use pip or poetry.
- ruff 0.8.4 for lint+format. mypy 1.13 with --strict. pydantic 2.9 for all DTOs.
- FastAPI 0.115, httpx 0.28 (async only). No requests, no aiohttp.
- LangGraph 1.0.x StateGraph + langgraph-supervisor 0.0.27. No legacy AgentExecutor.
- Anthropic SDK 0.40 (claude-sonnet-4-5-20251022 default; claude-opus-4-7 for judge).
- Qdrant client 1.12, Tantivy 0.22, Cohere 5.13, Voyage 0.3 (voyage-3-large, dim=256 Matryoshka).
- fairlearn 0.12 for audit primitives.
- MCP spec 2025-11-25 via mcp 1.6 + langchain-mcp-adapters 0.3.

## Architecture invariants
- Supervisor = single LangGraph StateGraph. Two entry modes: "seeker", "recruiter".
- Sub-agents are nodes, NOT separate processes: search → evaluation → fairness.
- Skill Registry = 5 MCP servers. Tools via langchain-mcp-adapters.
- State is MatchState TypedDict. Mutations return new dicts.

## Fairness contract (HARD)
- Every result list of length ≥ k MUST pass through fairness/audit.py before return.
- 4/5ths rule impact ratio < 0.80 → trigger DetConstSort rebalance, log violation.
- MinSkew@k computed over synthetic protected slices ONLY.
- NEVER infer demographics from real names. Only synthetic_protected module.

## Citation contract (HARD)
- Every match rationale must include ≥ 3 CitedSpan objects.
- Use citations={"enabled": True} on documents.

## Audit contract (HARD)
- Every supervisor invocation writes one row to audit_log with hash chain.

## Forbidden patterns
- print() in library code → use structlog 24.x.
- bare except / except Exception → name the exception.
- Hardcoded API keys → read from config Settings.
- requests, aiohttp → httpx only.
- pandas in hot path → polars or pure Python.
